  <static seed="1085" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicAlgebra/RationalFunctions/rationalFunctionDomain10.pg">
    <statement><p>Find the domain of the function <m>y</m> defined by <m>\displaystyle{y(x)=\frac{x - 8}{x^{5}}}</m></p>
<p><fillin characters="34" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>\left(-\infty ,0\right)\cup \left(0,\infty \right)</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>The only potential for an invalid input value would be if the denominator of this expression works out to <m>0</m>. Since the only number making the denominator <m>0</m> is <m>x=0</m>, the domain is <m>{\left(-\infty ,0\right)\cup \left(0,\infty \right)}</m>.</p>
</solution>
